title: Ecuadoran president declares armed conflict as gunmen storm TV studio
description: The TV station takeover was one of several attacks reported across the country on Tuesday, including attempts to to kidnap police officers and university students.

title: Democrats say Biden must notify Congress about Israel arms transfers
description: More than a dozen Senate Democrats say they will block President Biden’s request to bypass congressional notification on arms transfers to Israel.

title: France’s new prime minister is 34. Here’s what to know about Gabriel Attal.
description: President Emmanuel Macron appointed Gabriel Attal after Élisabeth Borne’s ouster. He is the youngest and first openly gay prime minister in modern French history.

title: Sinéad O’Connor death deemed natural by coroner, ruling out suicide
description: Irish singer-songwriter Sinead O’Connor died at a London residence on July 26, 2023. She was 56.

title: U.S. citizen arrested on drug charges in Russia
description: Robert Romanov Woodland, 32, was born in Russia and adopted by an American couple as a toddler. He returned to live in Russia in 2020 and is now jailed on drug charges.

title: South Korea bans dog meat trade as animal welfare attitudes shift
description: Dog farmers opposed the bill, but rights groups say eating dog meat has become less popular with the rise of pet ownership and concerns over animal welfare.

title: Blinken pushes Israel to ease fighting, consider post-war vision for Gaza
description: The top U.S. diplomat is presenting a plan for Gaza’s future to Israeli leaders and pushing the region to see the crisis as a potential inflection point in the conflict.

title: Settlers killed a Palestinian teen. Israeli forces didn’t stop it.
description: Israeli settlers killed three Palestinians in Qusra in the deadliest settler attack in the West Bank since the war began. Israeli troops didn’t forcefully intervene.

title: Australia bans Nazi salutes, swastikas after extremist right-wing protests
description: The ban, which came into effect this week, was proposed after protesters used Nazi salutes at rallies against immigration and trans rights in Melbourne last year.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Blinken to meet with Israeli leaders in hopes of stemming conflict’s spread
description: In a rare admission of a targeted killing in another country, Israel said it had killed a Hezbollah commander in southern Lebanon.

title: Israel’s Gaza war leads to a massacre of journalists
description: At least 79 journalists and media workers have been killed since the start of the war on Oct. 7, according to the Committee to Protect Journalists.
